Due to their small size, good photostability, and λ
                  ex-dependent photoluminescence (PL) emission, carbon nanodots (CDs) as fluorescent probes may potentially exhibit good properties [37–39]. Although there have been several studies on the application of CDs as fluorescent probes/sensors in bioimaging [40–49], there have been no reports of CDs fluorescent probes for Arg (Scheme 1
                  ).
